Here are both approaches:

**1. Register the route** in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public AppShell()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
}
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage** — two approaches:

```csharp
// Approach A: String query parameter (product ID only)
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B: Full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive data in the ViewModel** with `IQueryAttributable`:

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: receive string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, etc.
        }

        // Approach B: receive full object
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
            ProductId = product.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel** on `ProductDetailsPage`:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailsPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailsViewModel">
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailsViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>

    <VerticalStackLayout>
        <Label Text="{Binding Product.Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding ProductId}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

- **Approach A** (query string) — best when you only need a simple ID and will load the rest from a service. Values arrive as strings.
- **Approach B** (`ShellNavigationQueryParameters`) — best when you already have the object in memory and want to avoid a redundant lookup. The object arrives as-is (no serialization).
- `ApplyQueryAttributes` is called automatically by Shell — you can handle both approaches in the same method.
- Always `await` `GoToAsync` to avoid race conditions.
